# Rulestead demo — optional overrides for `docker compose up`
#
# You usually do NOT need this file. `scripts/demo/up.sh` auto-selects free host
# ports, namespaces the project per git branch, and prints the real URLs — use it
# when running alongside other demos. These variables are only for a bare
# `docker compose up` where you want to pin values by hand.
#
# Copy to `.env` (Compose auto-loads it) and edit as needed.

# Project namespace (containers/network/volumes get this prefix).
# COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME=rulestead

# Host ports published to 127.0.0.1. Change these if 4000/3000 are taken.
# DEMO_BACKEND_PORT=4000
# DEMO_FRONTEND_PORT=3000

# IMPORTANT: the Next.js frontend bakes this API base at BUILD time. If you
# remap DEMO_BACKEND_PORT, you must change this to match (host:port the BROWSER
# uses), or the frontend will call the wrong port. up.sh wires this for you.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FLAGS_API_BASE=http://localhost:4000
